<article class="post-3805 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-announcement entry"><div class="entry-content">
<div class="wp-block-columns">
<div class="wp-block-column">
<h3>eLearning Resources for Students</h3>



<p>We are working on a list of resources to assist your student with online eLearning Resources during this time away from the classroom. This list is being updated daily, please check back often.</p>



<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link has-text-color has-background has-vivid-cyan-blue-background-color" href="https://rivervalleyschools.org/elearning/" style="color:#ffffff">eLearning</a></div>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column">
<h3>Social-Emotional Supports &amp; Community Resources</h3>



<p>River Valley School District support staff are available for any student or family struggling at this time. </p>



<div class="wp-block-file">
<a href="https://rivervalleyschools.org/wp-content/uploads/River-Valley-School-District-Community-Resources-Google-Docs.pdf">River Valley School District Community Resources</a><a href="https://rivervalleyschools.org/wp-content/uploads/River-Valley-School-District-Community-Resources-Google-Docs.pdf" class="wp-block-file__button" download>Download</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator">
<h3>You are invited to a scheduled Zoom meeting.</h3>



<p><strong>Topic: River Valley Regular Board Meeting April 27, 2020<br>Time: Apr 27, 2020 06:30 PM Eastern Time (US and Canada)</strong></p>



<p><strong>Join Zoom Meeting</strong><br>The community is invited to join in on our Zoom meeting on April 27th.<br><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://us04web.zoom.us/j/76327342407?pwd=bTB0ZnBiMHBzclhtaDFVcC9wWlhVdz09" target="_blank">https://us04web.zoom.us/j/76327342407?pwd=bTB0ZnBiMHBzclhtaDFVcC9wWlhVdz09</a></p>



<p><strong>Meeting ID:</strong> 763 2734 2407<br><strong>Password:</strong> 4WZqRr</p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator">
<h2>Continuity of Learning Plan</h2>



<p>Although schools are closed and not providing in-person instruction, teaching and learning must continue. Michigan educators have been called to provide our students with continued learning.</p>



<p><a href="/RiverValleyCOLPlanApproved041520.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">View our Continuity of Learning and COVID-19 Response Plan</a></p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator">
<h3>The “River Valley Chuck Wagon” meal service will continue through the end of the school year. </h3>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><strong>The meal drop-off times are as follows:</strong><br>Sawyer Trinity Church, 11:00 am to 11:30 am<br>New Troy Community Center, 11:45 am to 12:15 pm<br>Galien Old Grocery Store Parking Lot, 12:30 pm to 1:00 pm<br>Three Oaks Elementary, 1:15 pm to 1:30 pm<br>Hidden Harbor Villas, 1:35 pm to 1:50 pm<br>Oakview Estates, 1:55 pm to 2:10 pm</p>



<p>-Meals will be distributed on Mondays and Fridays.<br>-Monday meal bags will include Monday lunch through Friday breakfast.<br>-Friday meal bags will include Friday lunch through Monday breakfast. <em>(Meal bags cannot be split up.  Parents must take the entire bag.  For any items that your child does not eat, we encourage you to look online for creative ways that these food items can be used.</em>)<br>-Meals are free to all students 18 and under regardless of home district. <br>-Families are reminded to remain in their vehicles.  Just let our staff know how many children you need meal bags for and they will hand them to you.</p>



